text: Fidel Wagner (17 March 1912 - 14 February 1945) was a German skier. He competed in the Nordic combined event at the 1936 Winter Olympics. He was killed in action during World War II. ==References== Category:1912 births Category:1945 deaths Category:German male Nordic combined skiers Category:Olympic Nordic combined skiers of Germany Category:Nordic combined skiers at the 1936 Winter Olympics Category:People from Oberallgäu Category:German military personnel killed in World War II Category:Missing in action of World War II
